<task id="UDSS-007" project="UI Dialog Shell Standardization">
  <metadata>
    <title>Move CreateProject wizard components to shared library, refactor to IDataService</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <phase>1</phase>
    <estimated-effort>6 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>shared-library, wizard, project, refactor</tags>
    <dependencies>UDSS-001, UDSS-002</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Extract the CreateProject wizard from the Corporate Workspace solution into the @spaarke/ui-components
    shared library, following the same pattern established by the CreateMatter extraction in UDSS-005.
    The CreateProject wizard includes provisioning components (SharePoint site provisioning, container
    setup) that must also be migrated. All direct Xrm.WebApi calls in projectService.ts must be
    refactored to use IDataService. The component must support an "embedded" prop for navigateTo modal
    hosting.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior TypeScript/React developer with Dataverse and SharePoint provisioning experience</role>

  <goal>
    CreateProjectWizard exists in @spaarke/ui-components/components/, accepts IDataService via props,
    supports embedded mode, includes provisioning components, and compiles cleanly.
  </goal>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">No direct Xrm.WebApi calls in shared library code — all data access must go through IDataService.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Follow the same extraction pattern established by CreateMatterWizard (UDSS-005) for consistency.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/CreateProject/</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step id="1">Read all files in src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/CreateProject/ to understand the component tree, provisioning flow, and service dependencies.</step>
    <step id="2">Create @spaarke/ui-components/components/CreateProjectWizard/ directory in the shared library.</step>
    <step id="3">Move component files from CreateProject/ to CreateProjectWizard/, renaming the root component (ProjectWizardDialog to CreateProjectWizard) and including all provisioning subcomponents.</step>
    <step id="4">Refactor projectService.ts to accept IDataService as a parameter instead of calling Xrm.WebApi directly. Update all CRUD and provisioning calls to use the injected service.</step>
    <step id="5">Update all internal imports to use shared library relative paths. Add "embedded" prop to control dialog shell rendering.</step>
    <step id="6">Export CreateProjectWizard and its props type from components/index.ts barrel.</step>
    <step id="7">Run tsc --noEmit to verify TypeScript compilation succeeds with zero errors.</step>
  </steps>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>CreateProjectWizard component exists in @spaarke/ui-components/components/CreateProjectWizard/.</criterion>
    <criterion>No direct Xrm.WebApi calls exist in any file within the CreateProjectWizard directory.</criterion>
    <criterion>projectService accepts IDataService and delegates all CRUD through it.</criterion>
    <criterion>Provisioning components are included and properly migrated.</criterion>
    <criterion>Component accepts "embedded" prop controlling dialog shell rendering.</criterion>
    <criterion>Component and props type are exported from components/index.ts barrel.</criterion>
    <criterion>tsc --noEmit passes with zero errors.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
